window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>All three entries in Hilary Mantel's award-winning Wolf Hall Trilogy, brought together for the first time in audio.</p> <p>In Hilary Mantel's Wolf Hall trilogy, one of our very best writers brings the opulent world of the Tudors to bloody, glittering life. It is the backdrop to the rise and rise of Thomas Cromwell: lowborn boy, charmer, bully, master of deadly intrigue, and, finally, most powerful of Henry VIII's courtiers. But the bloody theatre of Cromwell's ascension will leave no one unscathed.</p> <p>This collection includes expertly adapted versions of <i>Wolf Hall</i>, <i>Bring up the Bodies</i> and <i>The Mirror and the Light </i>alongside <i>The World of Wolf Hall</i>, a listening guide which explores the key themes and historical context of the novels, and offers listening group questions to discuss.</p> <p>Read by Dan Stevens, Julian Rhind-Tutt, Joseph Kloska, and Anna Bentinck.</p> <p>Winner of the Man Booker Prize 2009.&nbsp;</p> <p>Winner of the Man Booker Prize 2012.&nbsp;</p> <p>Winner of the Costa Book of the Year 2012.&nbsp;</p> <p>Shortlisted for the Women’s Prize for Fiction 2013.&nbsp;</p> <p>Shortlisted for the Orange Prize 2009.&nbsp;</p> <p>Shortlisted for the Costa Novel Award 2009.</p>"; 
